\[
\frac{d}{dx} \left( (x - 1)e^x + 1 \right) = e^x + (x - 1)e^x = x e^x
\]

This means that \((x - 1)e^x + 1\) is an antiderivative of \(x e^x\), so the integral from 0 to \(x\) is:
